description: Specifies the name of sensed data reported by a Spaceheat SCADA

value_descriptions.RelayState: The Telemetry reading belongs to ['Energized', 'DeEnergized'] (relay.energization.state enum).
value_descriptions.WaterTempCTimes1000: Water temperature, in Degrees Celcius multiplied by 1000. Example: 43200 means 43.2 deg Celcius.
value_descriptions.WaterTempFTimes1000: Water temperature, in Degrees F multiplied by 1000. Example: 142100 means 142.1 deg Fahrenheit.
value_descriptions.GpmTimes100: Gallons Per Minute multiplied by 100. Example: 433 means 4.33 gallons per minute.
value_descriptions.CurrentRmsMicroAmps: Current measurement in Root Mean Square MicroAmps.
value_descriptions.GallonsTimes100: Gallons multipled by 100. This is useful for flow meters that report cumulative gallons as their raw output. Example: 55300 means 55.3 gallons.
value_descriptions.VoltageRmsMilliVolts: Voltage in Root Mean Square MilliVolts.
value_descriptions.FrequencyMicroHz: Frequency in MicroHz. Example: 59,965,332 means 59.965332 Hz.
value_descriptions.AirTempCTimes1000: Air temperature, in Degrees Celsius multiplied by 1000. Example: 6234 means 6.234 deg Celcius.
value_descriptions.AirTempFTimes1000: Air temperature, in Degrees F multiplied by 1000. Example: 69329 means 69.329 deg Fahrenheit.
value_descriptions.ThermostatState: Thermostat State: 0 means idle, 1 means heating, 2 means pending heat
